This paper is about optimizing Prolog programs, which is a topic closely related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of abstract interpretation also suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization techniques could also be relevant to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
